article.headline: Georgetown 63, Delaware State 54
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP)-- Brandon Bowman scored a career-high 30 points and Georgetown used its pressure defense to survive a 63-54 scare from Delaware State Saturday. Georgetown (4-0) forced 28 turnovers thanks to its press and sloppy second-half ball handling by Delaware State (0-2). However, the Hornets held a 37-35 lead with 12:37 to play in the game when Jahsha Bluntt hit a 3-pointer from the wing. The Hoyas, who are now 31-1 all time against schools currently in the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference, responded with a 15-4 run, which Bowman capped by a three-point play that pushed the lead to nine. Courtland Freeman gave Delaware State trouble inside most of the afternoon finishing with a career-high 13 points and six rebounds Carlos Hawkins scored 11 to lead the Hornets, which held a 26-25 halftime lead after leading by as many as seven in the first half.
